# Force LF line endings for files parsed/executed inside Linux containers,
# regardless of the checking-out platform's `core.autocrlf` setting. This
# repo is actively developed on Windows (where `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites
# LF -> CRLF in the working tree on checkout by default) -- without this, a
# fresh checkout could silently reintroduce CRLF into e.g.
# `docker/vault-entrypoint.sh`, which then fails under `/bin/sh` inside the
# `vault` container (a stray `\r` on every line breaks shell parsing).
*.sh text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
*.hcl text eol=lf
